            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="784" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d784">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Juarez</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Romero</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Extract.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chihuahua</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-11">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 11, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Friend</hi>: * * * We also received the day
                        before yesterday the news of the total defeat of the confederate army on the
                        9th of April. The great pleasure this news afforded us was marrred by the
                        very sad impression which the shocking intelligence of President Lincoln’s
                        assassination produced upon us. That great misfortune has profoundly
                        impressed me, as Mr. Lincoln, who worked with so much-earnestness and
                        abnegation for the cause of nationality and freedom, was worthy of a better
                        fate than the poniard of a coward assassin. I do most earnestly hope that
                        Mr. Seward’s wounds would not be mortal, and that his son, too, may have
                        been saved. I beg of you to pay a private visit to Mr. Seward in my name,
                        expressing to him my grief for the misfortunes befallen upon him, and my
                        best wishes for his speedy and complete recovery.</p>
                <p>* * * * * * *</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>BENITO JUAREZ.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Señor <hi rend="smallcaps">Don Matias Romero</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
